// covariance_pair_tables.cc
// =============================================================================
// AUTO-GENERATED pair assignment tables for covariance_aie multi-tile split.
// =============================================================================
// Generated by round-robin assignment of the 231 upper-triangle (i,j) pairs
// of a 21x21 Hermitian matrix across 4 AIE tiles: tile = pair_index % 4,
// where pair_index enumerates pairs in the order (0,0),(0,1),...,(0,20),
// (1,1),(1,2),...,(20,20) -- the SAME order covariance_matrix.cpp's
// OUTER_I/OUTER_J nested loop produces (i from 0..20, j from i..20).
//
// This round-robin scheme (rather than splitting by contiguous row ranges)
// exists specifically to avoid load imbalance: a contiguous split would give
// tile 0 (rows 0-4) about 95 pairs while tile 3 (rows 16-20) gets only
// ~15 pairs, since row i has (21-i) pairs in the upper triangle. Round-robin
// gives every tile pairs of constant cost (1000 MACs each), so the 58/58/58/57
// split below translates almost exactly to 58/58/58/57 in real compute time.
//
// DO NOT hand-edit this file. If M_CH changes, regenerate with the Python
// script described in covariance_aie.h's header comment.
// =============================================================================

